<plot>Irving Belfer has turned his house into a museum filled with his own folk art and treasured collectibles. The newspapers have called him, "The Factory" and even the "Museum Man". Mr. Belfer lived through the hell of Hitler's reign during World War II, losing those he loved most. Theo Irving Belfer's art amazes everyone who comes to take the tour through his small home. It is Irving Belfer, himself, who is the diamond in the wooden sculptures.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?096794</url></doc>
